        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Handle Telegram flood waits",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- retry Telegram `FLOOD_WAIT` responses through one shared client-level policy for TData imports and Postbox remote-media reads\n- retry only the failed RPC so paginated scans keep their cursor and do not restart or duplicate rows\n- cap each server-requested wait at five minutes and each RPC at three retries; keep waits context-cancellable and report them on stderr\n- reserve the retry budget inside child RPC/download deadlines and return terminal policy errors that downstream gotd retry layers cannot re-catch\n- document the user-visible fix in `CHANGELOG.md` and the durable availability rule in `VISION.md`\n\n## Proof\n\n- `go test ./...`\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go mod verify`\n- `go build ./...`\n- focused retry, progress, cancellation, maximum-wait, retry-limit, timeout-budget, and pagination regressions\n- `$autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`: clean on exact head\n- bounded authenticated Postbox proof: 3 chats / 124 messages; 21/21 remote candidates attempted, 15 downloaded, 0 timeouts, 0 errors; no natural `FLOOD_WAIT` observed\n",
